{"word":"ναύτης","slug":"ναύτης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ναύτης</b></el> <el>(ναύτης, ου, ὁ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ναῦς'><el>ναῦς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>nauta, a seaman, sailor</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <el>ν. ὅμιλος</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a mate</i> or <i>companion by sea</i>, <el>ναύτην ἄγειν τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}